bib_record.title: Backward-angle anomalies in inelastic alpha-particle scattering on 40Ca.

free_txt: 11 detectors were mounted on the movable lid
of the scattering chamber. The effective aperture of
the detectors was about 1.5 degree including the
effect of the finite beam spot on the target.
To charge collection in a Faraday cup, two monitor
counters were used to normalize the data for different
The energy uncertainty of alpha-particle beam.
The relative error of the data points is
mainly given by the statistics of the counting rate.
mu-g/cm**2 was used. For angles smaller than 50
degrees a single isotopic target was used.
